==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Funicle
<hw>Fu"ni*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>funiculus</ets>, dim. of <ets>funis</ets> cord, rope: cf. F.
<ets>funicule</ets> funicle (in sense 2). Cf. <er>Funambulo</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small cord, ligature, or
fiber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The little stalk that attaches a
seed to the placenta.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Funicular</ent>⟦br⟧
